### Conflicts
Reviewers, this pull request conflicts with the following ones:

* [#14605](https://drahtbot.github.io/bitcoin_core_issue_redirect/r/14605.html) (Return of the Banman by dongcarl)
* [#14224](https://drahtbot.github.io/bitcoin_core_issue_redirect/r/14224.html) (Document intentional and unintentional unsigned integer overflows (wraparounds) using annotations by practicalswift)
* [#13864](https://drahtbot.github.io/bitcoin_core_issue_redirect/r/13864.html) (validation: Document where we are intentionally ignoring bool return values from validation related functions by practicalswift)
* [#13815](https://drahtbot.github.io/bitcoin_core_issue_redirect/r/13815.html) (util: Add [[nodiscard]] to all {Decode,Parse}[...](...) functions returning bool by practicalswift)

If you consider this pull request important, please also help to review the conflicting pull requests. Ideally, start with the one that should be merged first.
Concept ACK `maybe_unused` is a C++17 introduction, I assume it's ok to use it though based on preprocessor activation.
@Empact Yes, it is worth noting that both `clang++` and `g++` support `[[maybe_unused]]` also under `-std=c++11`. Luckily no need for wait for C++17 :-)

`BlockNotifyGenesisWait` uses unnamed args to mark them as unreferenced.
Should we name there or apply that here?
@ken2812221 Updated to address feedback. Please re-review :-)

+#if defined(__has_cpp_attribute) && __has_cpp_attribute(maybe_unused)
+#  define MAYBE_UNUSED [[maybe_unused]]
+#elif defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
comments.body: `__GNUC__` is also defined by clang. Don't have to check `__clang__`

it seems odd that this would be necessary in a declaration. instead of adding the attribute here, you could just remove the name of the parameter (just like for the second parameter). neither are used in the declaration anyway.
`ibd` seems to *always* be unused here. I think a better approach is to just remove the argument name
`title` appears to be unused as well. I think a better approach is to remove the parameter name.
